{
  "texts": [
    "Recommendation systems have gained widespread adoption in contemporary society to alleviate the overwhelming burden of information overload [5].",
    "Traditionally, researchers primarily focused on optimizing users' immediate responses (e.g.",
    "clicks) to maximize instant benefits [51].",
    "However, such a greedy recommendation strategy tends to cater to users' immediate interests excessively, neglecting long-term engagement [44] and even influencing the ecology negatively.",
    "For instance, some users will be confined within an echo chamber of preferred information and filter bubbles [17]."
  ]
}